search:.NET Core SignalR:.net core signa.content:
- Install SignalR using NuGet: `dotnet add package Microsoft.AspNetCore.SignalR`
- Add SignalR service to Startup.cs: `services.AddSignalR();`
- Configure SignalR in Program.cs or Startup.cs:
  ```csharp
  app.UseEndpoints(endpoints =>
  {
      endpoints.MapHub<ChatHub>("/chatHub");
  });
  ```
- Create a Hub class (e.g., ChatHub.cs):
  ```csharp
  public class ChatHub : Hub
  {
      public async Task SendMessage(string user, string message)
      {
          await Clients.All.SendAsync("ReceiveMessage", user, message);
      }
  }
  ```
- Connect to the hub from a client using JavaScript:
  ```javascript
  const connection = new signalR.HubConnectionBuilder()
      .withUrl("/chatHub")
      .build();

  connection.on("ReceiveMessage", (user, message) => {
      console.log(`${user}: ${message}`);
  });

  connection.start().then(() => {
      console.log("SignalR Connected.");
  });
  ```
- Key config options in Startup.cs:
  ```csharp
  services.AddSignalR(options =>
  {
      options.EnableDetailedErrors = true;
  });
  ```
- Latest versions: Ensure you use the latest compatible versions of .NET Core and SignalR.
